                                                                                                                                    TCS revenues top $4bn 

   OUR CORRESPONDENT 
        Ramadorai: Scaling heights 
   
	Mumbai, Jan. 16: Tata Consultancy Services (TCS), the countrys largest software company, today reported that its revenues in the first nine months of this fiscal topped $4 billion (Rs 17,168.36 crore).
 
	The software giant said its net profits during the third quarter ended December 31 had risen 19 per cent year-on-year to Rs 1,327 crore, and 6 per cent quarter-on-quarter.
 
	A clear focus on emerging markets and a diversified model clubbed with its global delivery model helped ratchet up its third quarter revenues 22 per cent year-on-year to Rs 5,923 crore. We are the first Indian company to cross $1.5 billion earnings in one quarter, said CEO and managing director S. Ramadorai.
 
	The company has seen balanced growth across geographies and sectors and several deals of over $50 million.
 
	Asked whether the imminent recession in the US economy would affect the fortunes of TCS, he said, The jury is still out on the slowdown. 
 
	We are cautiously confident about the future, he added.
 
	TCSs operating margins are up 2.3 per cent. We have seen 41 per cent growth in dollar terms and 24.3 per cent in rupee terms year-on-year, he said. Operating margin of the company was at 24.16 per cent, up 33 basis points over the previous quarter, and net income margin stood at 22.46 per cent, up 34 basis points.
 
	Shares to parent
 
	The TCS board cleared a proposal to allot non-convertible redeemable preference shares up to Rs 100 crore to Tata Sons, the promoters of the company, subject to the approval of shareholders. 
                                                            
